  "text": "The alerting scheduler tick is implemented across three files. ticker/ticker.go generates time ticks on a channel. schedule.go's schedulePeriodic() consumes these ticks and calls processTick() which determines ready rules, then runJobFn() dispatches evaluations. alert_rule.go's Eval() method detects overruns via a non-blocking channel read: if a previous evaluation is still pending, the dropped tick is returned. runJobFn() then logs 'Tick dropped because alert rule evaluation is too slow' and increments the EvaluationMissed metric. The exact phrase 'alert evaluation took longer than expected' does not appear verbatim; the actual warning is 'Tick dropped because alert rule evaluation is too slow' at schedule.go:438.",
